    Description

    The GroomPro deshedding brush is carefully engineered to guarantee gentle and effective deshedding grooming for your pet. It features a wide, shallow comb design to prevent penetration to the skin and to ensure that fur doesn't clog or break. It requires no pressure, so your pet won't feel any discomfort. The comb can be replaced when worn using the quick release no tool screw.

    Does it cut fur?

    At Rhykin we have developed a comb that has teeth which are placed wide apart and shallow with no cutting edge so as not to cut, drag or break the hair! The GroomPro comb is unique and cannot be found on any other type of grooming product!

    Is it suitable for all pets?

    Yes, it's perfect for dogs, cats, horses, and rabbits that shed but not recommended for pets under 6 months old or those with allergies.

    How do I use it?

     - Hold the GroomPro brush vertically against your pet's coat (not on its side or at an angle). 

     

    - Use short strokes to work the tool down the animal's body in the direction of hair growth. 

     

    - For optimal results, use the GroomPro brush regularly to maintain a healthy, shiny coat, and minimize shedding around your home.

    BRUSHING vs groompro

    While regular brushing helps detangle and remove surface debris, GroomPro goes deeper by targeting loose hair, dirt, and dander trapped in your pet’s undercoat.

     

    This deep-cleaning action promotes healthy air circulation through the coat, reducing the risk of bacteria build-up that can lead to skin conditions or infections.

     

    By using GroomPro, you’ll not only enhance your pet's overall health and comfort, but also minimize shedding around your home, keeping both your pet and living space clean and fresh!

    FAQ

    all of your questions, answered.

    How often should I use it?

    For best results, use the GroomPro 1-2 times a week for 10 to 20 minutes each session, though the actual time will vary depending on your pet’s breed, the condition of their coat, and the thickness of the pet’s individual coat. It may be necessary to use it more frequently during heavy shedding seasons.

    What happens if the comb wears out?

    The comb can be replaced! It's super easy to replace with a quick release, no-tool screw, ensuring your GroomPro always performs at its best.

    Is it durable?

    Durability was a big priority of ours. GroomPro is made from recycled plastic and stainless steel that is built to last and resist rust. 

    How do I contact you?

    If you have any questions or concerns, please contact our amazing customer support team at support@rhykin.com
